name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine OR the single dose of Johnson & Johnson. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register for the Pfizer vaccine.  You must be 18 or older for the Johnson & Johnson vaccine. (If 12-17 years old for the Pfizer vaccine, you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***

WALK-INS WELCOME UNTIL 10:45

name: Riverside Fire Authority Clinic
info: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose clinic**** and is by appointment or walk in. Please note: Johnson & Johnson vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements.  This clinic is located at and hosted by Riverside Fire Authority Station 6 in partnership with Lewis County Public Health and Social Services, WA Department of Health and WA National Guard. This is a walk-up location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill. It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: SPSCC 2011 Mottman Road SW, Olympia WA, 98512
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older.  

• This is a drive-thru clinic at South Puget Sound Community College (SPSCC), use the Crosby Blvd entrance. The clinic hours are 12:00PM- 7:00PM. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, dress with layers, if necessary. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Clark County PH- COVID Vaccine Site
address: Hathaway Elementary School 630 24th St, Washougal WA, 98671
info:
The Hathaway Elementary School vaccination site is providing 2nd dose Pfizer vaccines. 

Please do not arrive more than 10 minutes before your scheduled appointment. Arriving too early can lead to longer waiting times. 

You will be asked to remain at the vaccination site for 15 to 30 minutes after being vaccinated. Medical personnel will be monitoring you for possible reactions. Severe reactions are rare. 

What to bring:
•	Identification: If you have identification or some other proof of your date of birth, please bring it. This helps to ensure registration information is accurate. But ID is not required for vaccination. 
•	Face covering: Face coverings must be worn while at the COVID-19 vaccination site. 
•	Please wear a short-sleeved shirt or shirt with loose sleeves that can be pulled up. You will receive your COVID-19 vaccine in your upper arm. 

El sitio de vacunación de la Escuela Primaria Hathaway está proporcionando vacunas Pfizer en segunda dosis.

Por favor, no llegue más de 10 minutos antes de su cita. Llegar con demasiada antelación puede causar tiempos de espera más largos.

Se le pedirá que permanezca en el centro de vacunación de 15 a 30 minutos después de ser vacunado. El personal médico le vigilará para detectar posibles reacciones. Las reacciones graves son poco frecuentes.  

Qué debe traer:
•	Identificación: Si tiene un documento de identitificación, o documento con fecha de nacimiento, por favor tráigalo. Esto ayuda a asegurar que la información de registro es correcta. Pero no es necesario presentar un documento de identidad para la vacunación.  
•	Prenda para cubrirse la cara: Debe llevar una prenda para cubrirse la cara mientras esté en el centro de vacunación de COVID-19.  
•	Por favor, lleve una camisa de mangas cortas o una camisa con mangas sueltas que se puedan subir. Usted recibirá la vacuna contra la COVID-19 en la parte superior del brazo.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
